    "narrative": "The Austin Waves lineup is headlined by **Kyle Tucker**, whose 83.37 projection makes him the clear anchor for today\u2019s slate against Lorenzen. With an ideal 14% park boost and a favorable matchup against a middling starter, he is the engine of the outfield. He is flanked by **Miguel Vargas** (66.77) and **Jacob Wilson** (64.97), both of whom benefit significantly from high-efficiency spots in the order and park factors that play well into their respective profiles. **Miguel Vargas** is a particularly high-upside play today, as the combination of a 4.60 xERA opponent and a slow delivery behind the plate creates an ideal environment for his baserunning to bolster our scarcest category, stolen bases.\n\nWe have strategically prioritized high-efficiency spots over bench depth, with the decision to bench **Jackson Merrill** (54.06) being the most difficult call of the morning. While **Jackson Merrill** shows strong baseline capability, the daunting 2.35 xERA of the opposing pitcher makes him a lower-efficiency play compared to the likes of **Dominic Smith** or **Josh Lowe**, who face more forgiving arms. Our lineup remains heavily invested in platoon advantages; note that **Luis Robert Jr.** (63.25) carries a high ceiling despite a negative platoon shift, as the 19% SP skill advantage against Assad outweighs the tactical concern.\n\nRisk management remains paramount today, particularly with **Liam Hicks** (41.16) and **Gunnar Henderson** (53.28) facing sharper arms in Misiorowski and Cantillo, respectively. While **Gunnar Henderson**\u2019s raw talent usually forces a start, the 15% penalty due to the platoon disadvantage is a reminder that we are playing for daily efficiency caps. We are also keeping a close eye on **Drake Baldwin**, whose score of 65.63 is buoyed by his #2 spot in the order; any late lineup shuffling that pushes him down the order would trigger a re-evaluation of his total value. Ensure all rosters are set before first pitch to capitalize on these specific situational boosts.",
